# Wiki Statistics

## Goal
Generate a health and statistics dashboard for the {{config.project.name}} wiki.

<workflow>

<step n="1" goal="Count pages by type">
  <action>Scan `wiki/` filesystem and count: total pages, entities, concepts, source summaries, comparisons</action>
  <action>Count files in `raw/` by source type subdirectory</action>
  <action>Count files in `outputs/` by type (slides, reports, exports)</action>
</step>

<step n="2" goal="Analyze wiki activity">
  <action>Parse `wiki/log.md` for recent activity</action>
  <action>Count operations by type: ingestions, queries, lint passes, comparisons, exports</action>
  <action>Identify the most recently updated pages</action>
  <action>Calculate: average pages touched per ingestion, days since last ingestion</action>
</step>

<step n="3" goal="Assess cross-reference density">
  <action>Count total {{config.wiki.cross_ref_style}} links across all wiki pages</action>
  <action>Calculate average links per page</action>
  <action>Identify the most connected pages (hubs) and least connected pages (orphans)</action>
</step>

<step n="4" goal="Check source coverage">
  <action>Count raw sources vs. ingested sources (those with wiki/sources/ summaries)</action>
  <action>Calculate ingestion coverage percentage</action>
  <action>Identify un-ingested raw sources</action>
</step>

<step n="5" goal="Present dashboard">
  <action>Format a structured dashboard with sections: Page Counts, Activity Summary, Cross-Reference Health, Source Coverage, Top Hubs, Orphan Pages</action>
  <action>Include visual indicators where useful (e.g., coverage percentage)</action>
  <action>Suggest actionable next steps based on the statistics</action>
</step>

</workflow>
